<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include('components/header', { title: 'Data Transparency' }) %>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="../public/css/main.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div id="error">
        <div class="error err-fix">
            <h1 class="fancy-header-very-small">Data Transparency</h1>
            <p class="text-secondary mb-2">at Protagnst Media LLC</p>

            <p class="mt-3 mb-3 text-secondary text-center fs-6">
                We believe in making data reports available to everyone. We don't hide what we
                do with your data.<br />
                <hr class="mt-2" />
                Here's the data we RECIEVE when you login to our services:
            </p>

            <div id="recieved-data" class="mt-2">
                <table class="table table-dark">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Data</th>
                            <th scope="col">What we use it for</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Your E-Mail Address</th>
                            <td>We do not use this data at the moment. We may use it in the future to send e-mails to
                                successful applicants.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Your Discord ID</th>
                            <td>We use your Discord ID to check if you've used the app before, if you have, we load your
                                permission level (Member, Patreon Sub or Staff)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Your Discord Profile</th>
                            <td>The Discord API bundles your profile along with your ID. Your Profile includes but is
                                not limited to Your Username, Your Discriminator, Your Profile Picture/Banner</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Your Discord Authorization Keys</th>
                            <td>We recieve your Authorization Key and your Refresh Key when you Login with Discord. This
                                allows us to automatically add you to the correct Discord Server when your application
                                is accepted. <b>This does NOT allow us to access your account, send messages or read
                                    messages as you.</b></td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <hr class="mt-2" />

            <p class="mt-3 mb-2 text-secondary text-center fs-6">
                Here's the data we STORE when you login and use our services:
            </p>

            <div id="recieved-data" class="mt-2 mb-3">
                <table class="table table-dark">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Data</th>
                            <th scope="col">What we use it for</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Your Discord ID</th>
                            <td>We store your Discord ID as it is a unique value that differentiates you from everyone
                                else in the database.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Your Discord Authorization Refresh Key</th>
                            <td>We store your refresh key so that we can add you to a Discord Server when you are
                                accepted. The reason we keep your refresh key is because unlike your authorization key
                                (which expires after 7 days), your refresh key stays the same until you de-authorize the
                                app in your User Settings. <a class="text-decoration-none"
                                    href="/transparency/deauth">Click here for a guide on deauthorizing the app.</a>
                                    <br /><b>Note: We encrypt this piece of data as it can be sensitive. We use Crypto-AES 256 Bit Encryption with a private decryption key to avoid your data being leaked.</b>
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Your Permission Level</th>
                            <td>We store a permission level internally so that we can control what you access. We use
                                this to stop you from accessing a form you're not meant to <i>or finding your way into
                                    the staff dashboard without permission ðŸ‘®</i></td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <hr class="mt-2" />
            
            <div id="btnToolbar" class="btn-toolbar mt-2 mb-1" style="justify-content: center; display: flex;">
                <button type="button" id="btnSubmit" class="btn btn-primary btn-md me-2"
                    onclick="window.location.href = 'javascript:history.back()';"><i class="fa-solid fa-left-long"></i> Go Back</button>
                <button type="button" id="btnSubmit" class="btn btn-primary btn-md me-2"
                    onclick="window.location.href = '/support';"><i class="fa-solid fa-phone"></i> Contact Support</button>
            </div>

            <p class="text-secondary text-center fs-6">
                &copy; Protagnst Media LLC / Blaze Productions LLC 2022
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('components/loader') %>
</body>

</html>